All Arabic people are terrorists: This stereotype assumes that all Arabic individuals are violent and dangerous, which is not true and perpetuates discrimination and prejudice.
Arabic people are uneducated: This stereotype assumes that Arabic individuals lack intelligence or education, which is not true. Many Arabic people are highly educated and hold advanced degrees.
Arabic people are oppressive towards women: This stereotype assumes that Arabic individuals are sexist and mistreat women, which is not true for all Arabic people. While there may be gender inequality issues in some Arabic countries, this stereotype does not apply universally.
Arabic people are all Muslim: This stereotype assumes that all Arabic individuals are followers of Islam, disregarding the religious diversity within the Arabic community, which includes Christians and Jews as well.